{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"500g","heading":"Integration of electronic warfare into Tier 1 and Tier 2 joint training exercises","label":"500g Integration of electronic warfare into Tier 1 and Tier 2 joint training exercises","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptI/ch25","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Requirement","label":"a .—Requirement","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"During fiscal years 2026 through 2030, the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff shall require the integration of offensive and defensive electronic warfare capabilities into Tier 1 and Tier 2 joint training exercises.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Inclusion of Opposing Force","label":"b .—Inclusion of Opposing Force","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Chairman shall require exercises conducted under subsection (a) to include an opposing force design based on an intelligence assessment of the electromagnetic order of battle and capabilities of an adversary that is current as of the date of the exercise.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Waiver","label":"c .—Waiver","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a demonstration of electronic warfare capabilities; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a militarily significant threat from electronic warfare attack; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the integration of offensive and defensive electronic warfare capabilities into the exercise is cost prohibitive or not technically feasible based on the overall goals of the exercise.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Briefing","label":"d .—Briefing","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of such exercises planned and included in the budget submission for that fiscal year; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the extent to which offensive and defensive electronic warfare capabilities were integrated into the exercise;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"joint lessons learned;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"high interest training issues; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd%2F2%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"high interest training requirements; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fd%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an assessment as to whether offensive and defensive electronic warfare capabilities were part of an overall joint fires and, if so, a description of the manner in which such capabilities were incorporated into the joint fires.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Definitions","label":"e .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “electromagnetic order of battle” has the meaning given such term in Joint Publication 3–85 entitled “Joint Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations”, dated May 2020.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The terms “high interest training issue”, “high interest training requirement”, “Tier 1”, and “Tier 2” have the meanings given such terms in the Joint Training Manual for the Armed Forces of the United States (Document No. CJCSM 3500.03E), dated .April 20, 2015","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/e/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s500g/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs500g%2Fe%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “joint fires” has the meaning given such term in the publication of the Joint Staff entitled “Insights and Best Practices Focus Paper on Integration and Synchronization of Joint Fires”, dated July 2018.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
